I"í<p>By restricting a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/boltzmann-machine-is-a-universal-learning-machine">Boltzmann machine</a> to a low number of visibles and no hiddens, training them becomes tractable. Crucially, if <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/deep-learning-enables-simple-chained-transformations">chaining</a> multiple such machines through overlapping <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/cluster-index-quantifies-internal-external-connectivity">neuron clusters</a>, one obtains a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/supervised-learning-assumes-underlying-structure">neural network</a> resembling <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/deep-learning-is-consonant-with-empiricism">deep ones</a>.</p>
